div.div: Adds example table for typical personal assets and liabilities in Working Capital Calculator
Enhances Working Capital Calculator description and structure for clarity and user understanding

Refactors business partnership checklist categories
Updates the business partnership checklist categories to consolidate similar entries and improve clarity.
Removes redundant checklists related to valuation, investment strategy, risk management, and exit strategy, streamlining the category structure.
Modifies the ID and title of the "Business Partnership Research" checklist for consistency.

Refines financial calculator descriptions for clarity
Enhances the user interface of various financial calculators by updating headings and descriptions to provide clearer guidance on their functionalities.
Improves overall readability and user comprehension, ensuring that users can easily understand the purpose and benefits of each calculator.
Removes unnecessary styling elements for a cleaner look and incorporates more informative content to aid user decision-making.

Adds multiple financial ratio calculators
Introduces new calculators for financial ratios, including Current Ratio, Debt Service Coverage Ratio, Expense Ratio, Net Profit Margin, Operating Margin, Quick Ratio, Return on Assets, and Payroll Tax.
These tools enhance the application's functionality by aiding users in assessing their business's financial health through effective calculations.
Improves user experience with informative interfaces for each calculator, helping users make better financial decisions.
Adds business growth, operations, partnerships, customer service, financial planning, human resources, and marketing strategy checklists

Adds Cash Conversion Cycle Calculator component
Introduces a new calculator to compute the cash conversion cycle (CCC) for businesses.
The component allows users to input days inventory outstanding, days sales outstanding, and days payables outstanding, providing a calculated result along with an explanation of the CCC's significance.
This enhancement improves user capability to assess financial efficiency through a clear and interactive interface.

Adds cash flow management calculator component
Introduces a new calculator for managing cash flow, allowing users to input cash inflows, outflows, and starting cash balance.
Calculates net cash flow and ending cash position, helping users analyze financial health and ensure liquidity.
Provides a user-friendly interface with clear instructions and results display.

Adds cash flow forecasting calculator component
Introduces a new component for forecasting monthly cash flow, allowing users to estimate their business's cash position by inputting starting cash, monthly income, expenses, and payment timing.
Implements state management for user inputs and results, improving financial planning capabilities for businesses.

Adds business loan calculator component
Implements a new business loan calculator feature that allows users to estimate monthly payments, total interest, and total loan costs.
The component uses React hooks for state management and includes input fields for loan amount, annual interest rate, and loan term. It provides a clear user interface and straightforward calculations based on standard loan formulas.
Enhances the user experience by providing instant feedback on loan calculations.

Adds business expense tracker component
Introduces a new component for tracking and analyzing business expenses.
Users can input revenue and expenses, categorize them, and determine key metrics such as total expenses and expense ratios.
This feature enhances financial management capabilities within the application, providing insights for better budgeting decisions.

Adds Break-Even Point Calculator component
Introduces a new calculator component that allows users to determine the break-even point for their business operations.
The component captures fixed costs, variable costs per unit, and price per unit, then calculates key financial metrics such as contribution margin, break-even units, and break-even sales.
This enhancement aims to improve financial decision-making for users by providing a user-friendly interface for profitability analysis.
Renames Expense Tracker to Business Expense Tracker for clarity and consistency

Adds Inventory Turnover Ratio Calculator component
Introduces a new component for calculating the inventory turnover ratio, enhancing the finance calculators suite.
The component allows users to input cost of goods sold and average inventory, providing calculations for turnover ratio and days sales of inventory. It includes explanations and formulas to assist users in understanding the importance of the metric for inventory management.
This addition improves user experience by offering a tool for better inventory optimization and cash flow management.

Adds Profit Margin Calculator component
Implements a new Profit Margin Calculator to help users assess their business's financial health by calculating profit margins based on revenue and cost inputs.
The calculator provides an interactive UI for input, validates user data, and displays the calculated profit margin percentage. This tool enhances decision-making regarding pricing and cost management.

Adds sliders for input fields and improves layout
Introduces sliders for debt amount, interest rates, and loan terms to enhance user experience and interactivity.
Implements tables outlining typical terms and pros/cons of credit cards and personal loans for better information presentation.
Reorganizes the results display for improved readability and aesthetics.

Adds sliders for input fields in financial tool
Introduces slider components for salary, contribution, employer match, years to grow, expected annual return, current marginal tax rate, and retirement tax rate inputs.
This enhancement improves user experience by providing a more interactive way to adjust values, while maintaining the option to input values directly in the corresponding fields.

Adds sliders for input fields in income comparison tool
Implements sliders for key input fields such as hourly rate, hours per week, and estimated expenses to enhance user experience and improve input accuracy.
Introduces two tables displaying typical income and benefits as well as pros and cons of freelance versus full-time work, providing users with better insights for financial decisions.
Updates logic to automatically calculate and display estimated net annual income for both freelance and full-time options based on user inputs.
Removes the submit button, opting for real-time calculations instead for a more dynamic interface.

Adds debt vs investing comparison tables and sliders
Implements tables displaying typical debt and investment returns, along with pros and cons of each strategy.
Introduces sliders for user inputs, enhancing the interactive experience for the debt calculator.
These changes improve usability and provide clearer financial comparisons for users making informed decisions.

Implements interactive sliders for tuition input
Enhances the public vs. private college comparison tool by replacing numeric input fields with interactive sliders for tuition, room & board, fees, scholarships, and years.
This update improves user experience by allowing more dynamic input, ensuring real-time updates to calculations.
Additionally, introduces tables displaying typical college costs and pros & cons for public and private colleges, providing users with valuable context.
Removes the submit button functionality in favor of automatic calculations based on user input.

Adds sliders for input fields in investing vs saving tool
Implements slider components for user input fields, enhancing the user experience for setting initial amounts, monthly contributions, expected returns, and savings rates.
Introduces tables for typical returns and pros/cons of investing versus saving, providing users with clearer insights and comparative data.
Improves overall layout and design for better readability and interaction.

Adds car cost comparison tables and slider inputs
Introduces tables for typical car costs and pros and cons of new, used, and leasing options to enhance user decision-making.
Replaces numeric input fields with slider components for a more interactive experience when users adjust values for years, price, down payment, loan rate, loan term, insurance, maintenance, and depreciation.
Improves overall layout and presentation of results for better readability and user engagement.

Adds detailed tables and sliders for transportation cost comparison
Implements tables displaying typical transportation costs and pros/cons for various modes, enhancing user understanding.
Replaces input fields with sliders for better user experience in adjusting values for years, car price, down payment, loan rate, and other expenses.
Updates results display to a card-like format for improved visual clarity.

Enhances user interface and formatting for stock simulator
Improves the layout and user experience of the stock market learning simulator by updating the component structure and adding informative text.
Formats monetary values consistently using a dedicated utility function, enhancing readability across the application.
The changes aim to provide users with a clearer understanding of their cash balance, transaction history, and overall portfolio value in the simulator.

Adds stock selection functionality in portfolio table
Implements a new stock selection feature in the portfolio table.
Users can now select stocks directly from the table, enhancing interactivity and improving user experience. The stock selection handler is passed as a prop, allowing for better management of selected stocks.
This change facilitates easier portfolio management and decision-making for users.

Adds compound interest visualizer component
Implements a new React component for visualizing compound interest.
Users can input initial amounts, interest rates, monthly contributions, and duration in years to see how their investments grow over time.
Includes a line chart for visual representation and displays total contributions, interest earned, and final balance.
Adds article title to the finance articles page

Adds Rent vs Buy calculator component
Implements a new component that allows users to compare the total costs of renting versus buying a home over a specified period.
The tool calculates total renting costs considering annual rent increases and total buying costs including mortgage payments, property taxes, insurance, and maintenance.
This feature enhances the application's functionality by providing users with valuable financial insights.

Adds college cost comparison tool
Introduces a new component to compare the estimated net costs of attending public versus private colleges.
Calculates total costs based on user inputs for tuition, room & board, fees, scholarships, and years of attendance.
Provides recommendations based on the calculated net costs, enhancing user experience in financial decision-making for college education.

Adds HDHP vs Traditional Health Plan calculator
Introduces a new calculator component that allows users to compare estimated annual costs between a High-Deductible Health Plan (HDHP) and a Traditional Health Plan.
The component includes input fields for premiums, deductibles, out-of-pocket maximums, and expected medical expenses, providing a clear breakdown of net costs for each plan.
This addition enhances the financial decision-making tools available to users.

Adds freelance vs full-time income comparison tool
Implements a new component that allows users to compare estimated net annual income from freelancing versus full-time employment.
The tool calculates gross and net income based on user inputs for hourly rates, hours worked, benefits, and tax rates, providing a clear recommendation based on the calculated values.
This addition enhances the financial decision-making capabilities of the application.

Adds Fixed vs ARM Mortgage comparison tool
Implements a new component to compare fixed-rate and adjustable-rate mortgages.
Calculates monthly payments and total costs for both mortgage types, providing users with recommendations based on their input.
Includes validation for user inputs to ensure all values are non-negative and logically consistent before performing calculations.

Adds debt consolidation comparison tool
Implements a new tool to compare current debts against a proposed debt consolidation loan.
Calculates total interest from existing debts and evaluates potential savings from consolidation. The user can enter multiple debts, loan amount, interest rate, and term to receive an analysis of their options.
This tool enhances financial decision-making by providing clear insights into the benefits of debt consolidation.

Adds balance transfer vs paydown comparison tool
Introduces a new component to compare the financial impacts of balance transferring versus paying down credit card debt.
The tool calculates total interest and time to payoff for both options, providing users with personalized recommendations based on their input values.
This feature aims to help users make informed financial decisions regarding credit card management.

Adds PortfolioTable component to enhance portfolio display
Introduces a new PortfolioTable component that encapsulates portfolio rendering functionality, improving code organization and readability.
Replaces the inline portfolio table in the stock market simulator with the new component, which also adds features such as value change calculations and better separation of concerns for future maintenance.
Enhances user experience by providing a more informative and structured view of portfolio holdings.
